I would like to offer for sale a Yugoslavian M70 O-PAP AK-47 rifle. Chambered in 7.62x39. If you are looking for a well-built, rugged, good-looking AK, this is it! Perfect for shooting or showing off. Even has something for investors, as this M70 rifle is a limited Zastava factory production run from NOS parts, and is expected to increase in value comparable to other original factory barreled and receiver AK rifles that are no longer imported. 

Asking $790 cash FTF. Firm.

You can still buy these at Atlantic Firearms for $759 shipped (plus whatever you pay for transfers), see https://www.atlanticfirearms.com/component/virtuemart/shipping-rifles/zastava-ak-47-m70-pap-7-62x39-rifle-detail.html?Itemid=0, but once their stock runs out, these Yugo O-PAP rifles will only be available on the secondary market and prices will start to increase. Don't miss this opportunity to own this classic and iconic AK rifle! Whether you are a new owner and want a top-quality rifle for your first AK or a long-time collector looking to fill a hole in your AK collection, this rifle has something for you.

title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban Norinco Type 56-3 AK47, 7.62x39mm
postcontent:
For sale is a Pre-Ban Norinco Type 56-3 AK47 chambered in 7.62x39mm.  This rifle was purchased new in 1984 prior to the import bans, and these AKs from Norinco are considered to be some of the best made.  This is a full numbers-matching rifle, and additional pictures can be provided if needed.  The furniture is the stock reddish/brown phenolic "bakelite" material, and is fitted with the stock slant muzzle break.  I also have the stock cleaning kit for the buttstock, original nylon/leather sling, and the matching bakelite bayonet.  The tube insert in the stock for the cleaning kit is cracked, so the kit would rattle inside, but the spring hinged buttplate and compartment are still fully functional.  The barrel is still in great condition, and the rifle is still fully functional and ready to shoot or just be a collectible safe queen.

I am also including eight (8) 30-round magazines (all steel mags), an AK47 manual, an M16-style muzzle break, and a soft rifle case.

This is a rare piece, and is a very early import as it was manufactured before Norinco began stamping their logo and the model type onto the receiver.  This also features the "S" and "C" markings for the safety selector instead of the later "S" and "F" markings.  These are a great piece of history and will be rock solid for years to come.

Asking $1,650 for everything OBO, not looking for trades and will not split up the rifle and accessories.

The wear is consistent with something that spent a lot of time in a holster.  Mechanically it is perfect.  Locks up tight.  Shoots straight and every time.
Being an N frame this thing will make light .38 Special loads seem like you're shooting .22LR while it will also handle 180gr Buffalo Bore .357 Magnum heavy hitters.  You'll break before the gun does.
The action is nice and smooth and breaks cleanly.  Nice and worn in from a gun that has seen use and care over it's life.

Included with it is it's original small Magna grips, a set of the bigger S&W Combat grips, and a set of Pachmayr Presentation grips.  The Combat grips go for over $75 each when you can find them.  These are a bit used but they match the gun nicely and fill the hand much better than the Magnas.  The Pachmayr grips reduce the felt recoil nicely but aren't as visually appealing.

Honestly, I don't want to sell it.  It's a neat gun.  It's useful and it's also a rarer gun.  I've gotten the big Combat grips and I like it with them.  However unfortunately I have some other pressing needs.
That said I won't consider low ball offers.  Find a gun like this with all the extras for anywhere near my asking price.  Bet it's not a -3 either.  I've done a few searches and haven't found any -3's up for sale anywhere.

title: For Sale:  CCW Class June 7
postcontent:
Thank you for your interest in taking my Concealed Carry Handgun Course. 
Things to Know:
‚Ä¢	The class will start at 9:00 am sharp and last until 6:00pm
‚Ä¢	The class will be held at Hope Mills Recreation Center 5770 Rockfish RD Hope Mills, NC 28348.
‚Ä¢	The range is off site about 15 miles from the Recreation center.  We will break around 12 for the qualification.
Things you should Bring:
‚Ä¢	An Open Mind and Willingness to Learn
‚Ä¢	Notebook and a pen 
‚Ä¢	A Handgun and 50 rounds of factory ammo.  (Preferably the handgun you plan to carry)***If you do not have a handgun I have two handguns that can be rented for $20.  This will include the ammo for the handgun****  
‚Ä¢	Eye and Ear Protection ( If you do not have your own I will have some on site for you to purchase)
‚Ä¢	Any snacks or drinks you may want during the course of the day.
‚Ä¢	$50 cash to cover the cost of the class.
‚Ä¢	A holster for your handgun (extra magazines for your handgun are a plus but not necessary)  
Topics that will be Covered:
‚Ä¢	Legal Issues
‚Ä¢	Handgun Safety
‚Ä¢	Handguns/Selection
‚Ä¢	Handgun Fundamentals
‚Ä¢	Marksmanship Fundamentals
‚Ä¢	Carrying Concealed safety Issues
‚Ä¢	Presentation Techniques (Drawing your Handgun)
‚Ä¢	Cleaning and Maintenance
‚Ä¢	Ammunition
‚Ä¢	Proficiency test
After completion of the course and receiving your certificate you can apply to the sheriff‚Äôs office in the county you reside. Be sure to take your original training certificate with you when you go to apply. The Sheriff‚Äôs office charges $90 for a criminal background check and mental health check. Most Sheriff‚Äôs offices require you to pay in cash and EXACT change so make sure you find out ahead of time. Fees can vary somewhat so be sure to check with the Sheriff‚Äôs office in your county. If you are approved, your permit will be issued in less than 90 days. It is valid for 5 years. As of January 1,2010, the Sheriff's office is required to send you a renewal notice. The notice will be mailed to the address listed on your permit, so if you move contact the Sheriff's Office with your new address. You must appear at the county sheriff's office and pay the renewal fee. 
******* NO MORE PISTOL PERMITS ********
Under North Carolina Law, the holder of a valid North Carolina Concealed Carry permit can use this permit to purchase handguns in the state of North Carolina. Obtaining a purchase permit is no longer required.

If you have any other questions please feel free to contact me by phone REDACTED  or email  REDACTED
See you on the Range!
Matt Wentzel

Features: 
Bushnell Elite 3200 Rifle Scopes¬†feature resettable fingertip adjustments for windage and elevation with repeatable audible clicks. They also feature 1-piece hammer forged aluminum titanium alloy tubes and multi-coated lenses that have been treated with Bushnell's Rainguard coating. This scope features 1/10 milliradian (MIL) windage and elevation turrets and a Mil-dot reticle; this is also known as MIL/MIL. The combination of these two features enables the shooter to make quick and precise corrections. By using the Mil-dot reticle to measure how far off the shot is in MILs, each dot is 1 MIL apart, the shooter does not need to convert milliradians to minutes of angle in order to correct the point of aim. With traditional 1/4 MOA turrets, if the point of impact is measured to be 1.5 MILs low the shooter needs to convert the MILs to MOA and then adjust the turrets which can be confusing. With a¬†MIL/MIL¬†rifle scope if the shot is 1.5 mils low then the shooter simply turns the turret 1.5 mils or 15 clicks. The mil-dot reticle can also be used to determine how far away an object of known size is. These features are usually only found in very expensive scopes, but MidwayUSA has worked with Bushnell to bring you this exclusive high quality rifle scope at a very reasonable price.¬†Bushnell Elite 3200 Rifle Scopes¬†are waterproof, fogproof and shockproof and covered by the Bushnell limited lifetime warranty.
